Two factors that are important in an argument are clarity and credibility. I chose clarity because to have a meaningful argument it must be clear exactly what you are arguing about. The wording must be chosen correctly to not leave a chance to be misconstrued by others due to definition or leaving it open ended. Credibility is extremely important because whoever is chosen to speak for a certain field needs to have knowledge of what they are speaking about. For instance, you wouldnâ€™t want a high school math teacher to discuss an autopsy for a judge, you would want to hear from a mortician.
